post_cb({"34389037": {"ParentId": "34388808", "CommentCount": "1", "Body": "<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_34388808_34389037_0\"><strong>[dcl.init.ref]/1</strong> A variable declared to be a <code>T&amp;</code> or <code>T&amp;&amp;</code>, that is, \"reference to type <code>T</code>\" (8.3.2), shall be initialized by an object, or function, of type <code>T</code> or by an object that can be converted into a <code>T</code>.</p>\n<p id=\"so_34388808_34389037_1\"><strong>[dcl.init.ref]/5</strong> A reference to type \"<code>cv1 T1</code>\" is initialized by an expression of type \"<code>cv2 T2</code>\" as follows:</p>\n<p id=\"so_34388808_34389037_2\">...</p>\n<p id=\"so_34388808_34389037_3\">(5.2.2.2) -- If <code>T1</code> is a non-class type, a temporary of type \"<code>cv1 T1</code>\" is created and copy-initialized (8.5) from the initializer expression. The reference is then bound to the temporary.</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "OwnerUserId": "1670129", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "34389037", "Score": "4", "CreationDate": "2015-12-21T04:38:33.747", "LastActivityDate": "2015-12-21T04:38:33.747"}, "34388808": {"CommentCount": "5", "ViewCount": "67", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "2486888", "CreationDate": "2015-12-21T04:06:05.900", "LastActivityDate": "2015-12-21T04:38:33.747", "Title": "Type change in rvalue reference", "AcceptedAnswerId": "34389037", "LastEditDate": "2015-12-21T04:17:11.883", "Id": "34388808", "Score": "3", "Body": "<p>May I know why this piece of code is valid.Thanks.</p>\n<pre><code>  double i=5;//int i=5 will invalidate this piece of code\n    int &amp;&amp; r1=i;\n    std::cout&lt;&lt;r1&lt;&lt;std::endl;\n</code></pre>\n", "Tags": "<c++><language-lawyer><rvalue-reference>", "OwnerUserId": "5405040", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_34388808_34389037_0": {"section_id": 3317, "quality": 0.8571428571428571, "length": 12}, "so_34388808_34389037_1": {"section_id": 3321, "quality": 0.6666666666666666, "length": 6}, "so_34388808_34389037_3": {"